You can get an OpenAI API key by creating an account on the OpenAI Platform and generating a new key in your user settings.

Here are the step-by-step instructions.

1. Create an OpenAI Account
First, you need an account on the OpenAI developer platform.

Go to the OpenAI platform website: platform.openai.com.

Click "Sign up" and create an account using your email, Google, or Microsoft account. You may need to verify your phone number.

Note: This is different from a regular ChatGPT account, although you can use the same login credentials. The key is only available on the developer platform.

2. Navigate to the API Keys Section
Once you are logged in, find the API keys page.

Click on your profile icon or name in the top-right corner of the page.

From the dropdown menu, select "View API keys".

Alternatively, you can go directly to the API keys page: platform.openai.com/api-keys.

3. Generate Your New API Key üîë
On the API keys page, you can create and manage your keys.

Click the "+ Create new secret key" button.

You will be prompted to give the key an optional name. This is highly recommended to help you remember which application uses which key (e.g., "My Chatbot Project").

Click "Create secret key".

4. Copy and Store Your Key Securely ‚ö†Ô∏è
A dialog box will appear showing your new API key.

This is the only time you will be able to see the full key. For security reasons, OpenAI will not show it to you again.

Click the copy icon to copy the key to your clipboard.

Store it in a secure location immediately, like a password manager or an environment variable file (.env) for your project.

Important: Treat your API key like a password. Never share it publicly, post it online, or commit it to a public code repository like GitHub.

5. Set Up Billing Information
To use the API beyond the initial free trial credits, you'll need to set up a payment method.

Go to the "Billing" section in the left-hand navigation menu.

Click "Add payment details" and set up a prepaid credit balance or a monthly plan.

That's it! You can now use your API key to make requests to the OpenAI API.











